# ARCANE Backend

The backend service for the ARCANE D&D NPC Management System.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/ARCANE.git
cd ARCANE/backend
```

2. Create a virtual environment and activate it:
```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
```

3. Install the package in development mode:
```bash
pip install -e .
```

## Running the Server

1. Start MongoDB:
```bash
mongod --dbpath ./data/db
```

2. Start the Flask server:
```bash
python wsgi.py
```

The server will start on http://localhost:5000.

## Running Tests

1. Run unit tests:
```bash
pytest tests/unit
```

2. Run integration tests:
```bash
pytest tests/integration
```

3. Run manual tests:
```bash
python tests/manual_test.py
```

## API Documentation

### NPC Endpoints

- `POST /npcs/`: Create a new NPC
- `GET /npcs/`: Get all NPCs
- `GET /npcs/{npc_id}`: Get a specific NPC
- `PUT /npcs/{npc_id}`: Update an NPC
- `DELETE /npcs/{npc_id}`: Delete an NPC
- `POST /npcs/{npc_id}/equipment`: Add equipment to an NPC
- `POST /npcs/{npc_id}/spells`: Add a spell to an NPC

### Campaign Endpoints

- `POST /campaigns/`: Create a new campaign
- `GET /campaigns/`: Get all campaigns
- `GET /campaigns/{campaign_id}`: Get a specific campaign
- `PUT /campaigns/{campaign_id}`: Update a campaign
- `DELETE /campaigns/{campaign_id}`: Delete a campaign

### Encounter Endpoints

- `POST /encounters/`: Create a new encounter
- `GET /encounters/`: Get all encounters
- `GET /encounters/{encounter_id}`: Get a specific encounter
- `PUT /encounters/{encounter_id}`: Update an encounter
- `DELETE /encounters/{encounter_id}`: Delete an encounter

